3.1 Arithmetic Logic Unit (ALU)

Performs:
Arithmetic operations: + − × ÷
Logical operations: AND OR NOT XOR
Comparisons: < > =
Uses operands from registers and produces results stored back in registers.

3.2 Control Unit (CU)
Directs the operation of the processor.

Responsibilities:
Fetches instructions from memory
Decodes instructions
Generates control signals to execute them
Acts as a traffic controller inside the CPU.

3.3 Registers
Small, fast storage inside the CPU.

Hold:
Instructions
Data
Addresses
Intermediate results

Examples:
PC (Program Counter) – address of next instruction
IR (Instruction Register) – current instruction
Accumulator
General-purpose registers
